  "title": "Marketing and Event Executive",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a creative, hands-on Marketing Executiveto support K.STAR’s brand growth, promotions, and customer engagement.</p><p>This role works closely with the Founder and Operations Teamto execute marketing campaigns, manage content, and strengthen K.STAR’s premiumentertainment brand across digital and offline touchpoints.<br /></p><p>Key Responsibilities:<br /></p><p><strong>Brand & Content Marketing       </strong></p><p>Execute KSTAR   brand messaging across social media, Website and in-store materials.</p><p>Assit in  Content creation including: </p><ul><li>Short media posts</li><li>Short-form video</li><li>Poster and visual assets</li><li>Caption EDMs and simpler Copywriting </li></ul><p><strong>Social Media & Digital Marketing</strong></p><p>Manage daily content posting on platforms such as</p><ul><li> Instagram/Tikrok/Xiaohongshu(RED)/Wechat </li><li>Monitor engagement, comments, DMs and customer interactions</li><li>Support  digital marketing initiative including: </li></ul><ul><li>paid advertisementsPromotionsand influencer KOL collaborations (if any)</li></ul><p><strong>Campaigns & Promotions </strong></p><p>Support marketing Campaigns for:</p><ul><li>Membership promotions</li><li>Corporate Clients & events </li><li>Seasonal festive campaigns  </li></ul><ul><li> Assist in on-ground promotion and event execution</li></ul><p><strong>Corporate & Partnershipsupport  </strong></p><ul><li>Prepare simple marketing material for corporate Clients (PDF decks, visuals, post)     </li></ul><p><strong>Support branding:</strong></p><ul><li> Corporate eventsTeam-building activitiesand private functions.Assist in partnership and collaboration marketing initiatives.</li></ul><p><strong>Performance Tracking</strong></p><ul><li>Track basic marketing metrics such as </li><li>ReachEngagement Leads </li><li>Bookings</li><li>Andprepare simple reports and insights for continuous improvement.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or bachelor’s degree in marketing, Mass Communications, Medial or related field.1 – 3 year experience (Fresh graduates with relevant internships of portfolio may considered)</li><li>Familiar with Instagram, TikTok, Xiaohongshu (RED), and WeChat  </li><li>Basic content creation skills (copywriting, short videos, simple visuals) </li><li>Comfortable using tools like Canva, CapCut, or similar</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Hands-on, proactive, and able to work in a fast-paced environment  </li><li>Flexibility to work irregular hours, including evenings and weekends, as required for events.</li></ul>",
